@NODE "Z" "Additive Congruental Alghorythm"

            Additive Congruental Alghorythm
           »»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»
 
 This algorythm encodes randomly... And it's good because of it's high
 speed... Nobody could ever decrypt a triple crypted file with three
 different keys... If you try it... You have to try
 9.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999.999
 different keys if you ONLY use digits.... Even more if you use letters or
 things like !@$%&, and it's casesensitive, so there are 2 tries for every letter :)
 Have fun :)

@ENDNODE
